# Examples of adding native language names to .resx files

## For English (Strings.resx)
Add this entry near the beginning of the <root> element's content:

```xml
<data name="__LanguageNativeName" xml:space="preserve">
  <value>English</value>
</data>
```

## For German (Strings.de.resx)
Add this entry near the beginning of the <root> element's content:

```xml
<data name="__LanguageNativeName" xml:space="preserve">
  <value>Deutsch</value>
</data>
```

## For Spanish (Strings.es.resx)
Add this entry near the beginning of the <root> element's content:

```xml
<data name="__LanguageNativeName" xml:space="preserve">
  <value>Español</value>
</data>
```

## For any new language file (e.g., Strings.fr.resx for French)
Add this entry near the beginning of the <root> element's content:

```xml
<data name="__LanguageNativeName" xml:space="preserve">
  <value>Français</value>
</data>
```

## Where to add it in the file
Add the entry immediately after the XML header and schema definitions, 
right before the first existing <data> element. A good location is after 
the <xsd:element name="root"> section and before your first string entry. 